<br>
Especially after zone drops just have your people in the zone of choice spamming '[x] blah is camped by [y]'. There can be no confusion then. After a server bounce you know that the mob will be up within 24 hours, so its the perfect time to do this. Waiting days after that may suck, but at least after a bounce it't not a bad camp. (well as they go anyway, compare it to rage)<br>
<br>
The whole epic system stinks actually, it should be awarded according to work the player does, not be a competition amongst players. I'll play Tribes if I want to compete with other players, and have a lot more fun. Or play on VZ or RZ. (as I used to)<br>
<br>
But I think people may have to become as serious as the clerics are if they want to complete epics. If I zone in and see 'Sev camped by VoR for Conana' I will say 'Hail VoR! Let me know if you need a hand with the big lizard'. Epics are a special case and if it takes lists for epic mobs I don't see it as a horrible thing. But that will have to be up to the respective classes in question.<br>
<br>
But as it stands epic mobs are treated only slightly better than the AC in SRO. As it stands people in guilds with burners have a decided edge in getting their epics completed. As it stands any burner is obliged to do all she can to help her guildmates complete epics.<br>
